article.headline: Long Island 82, Monmouth 78
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Eugene Kotorobai scored 18 points and Jaytornah Wisseh added 16, including six free throws in the final 2:36, and LIU held off Monmouth 82-78 Tuesday night. Tyrone Mattison added 13 points for the Blackbirds (10-17, 6-10 Northeast), who led 38-33 at halftime. Dejan Delic scored 27 points, 19 in the second half, to lead the Hawks (12-16, 7-9). Marques Alston added 18. A three-point play by Paska Morkeliunas gave LIU a 29-16 lead at 8:37 of the opening half. Delic then sparked a 12-2 run with six points to pull Monmouth to 31-28 at 3:15. No more than five points separated the two teams in the first 12 minutes of the second half. Monmouths last lead, 57-55, came on Delic's 3-pointer at 11:12. The Blackbirds took the lead for good, 73-71, on a layup by Wisseh at 2:36. Wisseh then sealed the win by scoring six of LIUs final nine points, all from the foul line.
